item.title: 沃尔玛支持的 PhonePe 准备在印度股市首次亮相
item.description: 沃尔玛支持的印度金融科技公司 PhonePe 周四表示，该公司正开始为在印度证券交易所公开上市做准备。【原文：Walmart -backed Indian fintech firm PhonePe is beginning preparatory steps for a public listing on the country's stock exchanges, the company said on Thursday.】

item.title: CenterPoint 与同行一起提高资本支出计划，以满足数据中心的电力需求
item.description: CenterPoint Energy 公司周四将其资本支出计划提高了 5 亿美元，以加强电网建设，应对全国各地新建数据中心激增的电力需求。【原文：CenterPoint Energy on Thursday increased its capital expenditure plan by $500 million to strengthen its electricity grid to handle the surging demand for power from new data centers coming up across the country.】

item.title: 富达为财富经理推出两款全 ETF 模型投资组合
item.description: 富达投资公司（Fidelity Investments）周四表示，该公司已推出两款全 ETF 模型投资组合，供财富管理公司在构建客户投资组合时从快速增长的基金阵营中寻找帮助。【原文：Fidelity Investments said on Thursday that it has launched two all-ETF model portfolios for use by wealth management firms looking for help winnowing through the rapidly growing array of funds to construct client portfolios.】

item.title: 巴西 Natura &Co 公司与 IG4 公司就潜在的雅芳交易进行谈判
item.description: 巴西化妆品制造商 Natura &Co 周四表示，该公司正在与资产管理公司 IG4 就可能出售雅芳在拉丁美洲以外地区的业务进行独家谈判，但指出谈判仍处于早期阶段。【原文：Brazilian cosmetics maker Natura &Co said on Thursday that it is in exclusive talks with asset manager IG4 for the potential sale of Avon's operations outside Latin America, but noted the negotiations were still at an early stage.】

item.title: 基础设施需求强劲，广达第四季度利润超出预期
item.description: 能源承包商广达服务公司（Quanta Services）周四第四季度利润超出预期，原因是其电力和基础设施相关服务的需求增加，股价在收盘前上涨了 7%。【原文：Energy contractor Quanta Services beat fourth-quarter profit estimates on Thursday, on higher demand for its services related to power and infrastructure, sending shares up 7% before the bell.】

item.title: 马来西亚称东盟计划召开美国峰会讨论关税问题
item.description: 马来西亚外交部长周四表示，东南亚集团东盟计划与美国举行一次峰会，以便其成员国就美国计划征收的关税发表意见。【原文：The Southeast Asian bloc ASEAN plans to hold a summit with the United States so its member countries can present their views on planned U.S. tariffs, Malaysia's Foreign Minister said on Thursday.】

item.title: 沃尔玛预测 2026 财年销售收入低于预期，原因是支出谨慎
item.description: 沃尔玛周四预计，截至2026年1月的财年销售额将低于华尔街目前的预期，这表明这家全球最大的零售商预计，在经历了几个季度的稳健增长后，疲于通胀的消费者将有所回落。【原文：Walmart on Thursday forecast sales for the fiscal year ending January 2026 below Wall Street's current estimates, signaling the world's largest retailer expects inflation-weary consumers to pull back after several quarters of solid growth.】

item.title: 炼油利润率下降导致 HF Sinclair 亏损超过预期
item.description: 受炼油利润下滑和全球产能增加的影响，炼油商 HF Sinclair 周四公布的第四季度亏损大于预期。【原文：Refiner HF Sinclair posted a bigger-than-expected fourth-quarter loss on Thursday, hurt by a slump in refining margins and a rise in global capacity.】

item.title: FibroGen 向阿斯利康出售中国业务，交易价值 1.6 亿美元
item.description: FibroGen 周四表示，已将其中国业务以约 1.6 亿美元的价格出售给阿斯利康。【原文：FibroGen said on Thursday that it has sold its China unit to AstraZeneca for about $160 million.】

item.title: 玩具制造商孩之宝预测全年收入低于预期
item.description: 孩之宝（Hasbro）公司周四预测 2025 年的收入将低于华尔街的预期，因为这家美国玩具制造商面临着对《星球大战》（Star Wars）动作人偶和奈飞（Nerf）枪支等产品的需求低迷。【原文：Hasbro forecast 2025 revenue below Wall Street estimates on Thursday, as the U.S. toymaker faces subdued demand for its products such as Star Wars action figures and Nerf guns.】

item.title: 坎帕里（Campari）确认为恢复财务健康进行组织结构调整
item.description: 意大利酒业集团达维德-坎帕里（Davide Campari）周四表示，需要做出一些 "艰难的决定，如组织重组"，以确保集团恢复中长期财务健康。【原文：Italian spirits group Davide Campari said on Thursday it needed to take some "tough decisions, such as organizational restructuring" to ensure the group's return to medium and long-term financial health.】

item.title: 早间新闻贸易和乌克兰紧张局势加剧，美联储出现变数
item.description: Mike Dolan 展望美国和全球市场的未来一天【原文：A look at the day ahead in U.S. and global markets from Mike Dolan】

item.title: 美国石油和生物燃料组织联合敦促特朗普新任环保局提高生物燃料强制要求
item.description: 据路透社看到的一封信称，美国石油和生物燃料集团本周联合起来，敦促特朗普新政府增加可再生燃料的用量，这些燃料必须在 2026 年及以后掺入美国的燃料组合中。【原文：U.S. oil and biofuel groups banded together this week to urge the new Trump administration to increase volumes of renewable fuels that must be blended into the nation's fuel mix in 2026 and beyond, according to a letter seen by Reuters.】

item.title: 美国公司将美元债券换成欧元以降低融资成本
item.description: 银行家和企业顾问表示，拥有海外业务的美国公司正在利用欧元的低利率来削减债务融资成本，并通过对冲策略来减轻利率上升带来的打击，如果美联储继续暂停降息，而其他央行不降息，预计这种对冲策略将会扩大。【原文：U.S. companies with overseas operations are taking advantage of lower rates in euros to slash their debt funding costs and soften the blow of higher interest rates with a hedging strategy that is expected to expand if the Fed continues to pause rate cuts and other central banks do not, bankers and corporate advisers said.】

item.title: 消息人士称，谷歌即将在印度选址开设美国以外的首家零售店
item.description: 三位熟悉内情的消息人士称，Alphabet 公司旗下的谷歌公司即将决定在印度这一重要市场开设其在美国以外的首家实体零售店。【原文：Alphabet Inc's Google is close to deciding on locations in its key market of India where it will open its first physical retail stores outside the United States, three sources familiar with the matter said.】

item.title: 日元飙升，黄金闪耀，股市再创新高
item.description: 周四，交易员们纪念 COVID 首次震撼全球市场五年，以及唐纳德-特朗普重返白宫开始撼动全球秩序一个月--有很多事情值得关注。【原文：Traders were marking five years since COVID first rocked world markets and one month since Donald Trump's return to the White House started shaking up the global order on Thursday - and there was plenty to keep tabs on.】

item.title: 加拿大泰克公司铜产量强劲，第四季度利润超出预期
item.description: 加拿大矿业公司泰克资源公司周四公布的第四季度利润超出分析师预期，主要得益于其智利铜矿铜产量的增加。【原文：Canadian miner Teck Resources beat analysts' estimates for fourth-quarter profit on Thursday, helped by higher copper production volumes at its Chile mine.】

item.title: 空中客车公司首席执行官暗示将成立类似 MBDA 的合资企业，以实现欧洲航天合并
item.description: 空中客车公司首席执行官周四表示，如果与泰雷兹公司和莱昂纳多公司的太空合并谈判能促成类似MBDA欧洲导弹项目的合资企业，他将感到高兴，并希望欧盟反垄断监管机构能采取比过去宽松的立场。【原文：The CEO of Airbus said on Thursday he would be happy if space merger talks with Thales and Leonardo led to a venture like the MBDA European missile project and hopes EU antitrust regulators will take a looser stance than in the past.】

item.title: 贸易部称鼓励外国品牌重返俄罗斯 "不明智
item.description: 工业和贸易部表示，鼓励外国品牌重返俄罗斯将是 "不明智的"，该部希望支持国内公司，因为这些公司已经介入，填补了西方同行离开后留下的空白。【原文：Encouraging foreign brands to return to Russia would be "ill-advised," according to the industry and trade ministry, which wants to champion domestic companies that have stepped in to fill the gaps left by departing Western counterparts.】

item.title: 涨势扩大，投资者寻找 "隐蔽 "的防御策略
item.description: 除了在欧洲市场上表现抢眼的传统国防类股票外，投资者还在寻找有望从该地区军费开支增长中获益的廉价工业公司。【原文：Investors are looking beyond the traditional defence stocks that have emerged as star performers in the European market for cheaper industrial companies poised to benefit from increased military spending in the region.】

item.title: 阿里巴巴第三季度收入超出预期
item.description: 中国阿里巴巴集团控股公司（Alibaba Group Holding）周三公布的第三季度营收超出华尔街预期，原因是年末购物销售强劲，吸引注重成本的消费者的战略取得成功。【原文：China's Alibaba Group Holding on Wednesday topped Wall Street expectations for third-quarter revenue, on strong year-end shopping sales and the success of its strategy to attract cost-conscious consumers.】

item.title: 市场评估关税和地缘政治风险，期货下跌
item.description: 美国股指期货周四下跌，原因是在美国总统唐纳德-特朗普再次发出关税威胁后，投资者回避风险，而地缘政治忧虑和美联储的谨慎态度进一步打击了市场情绪。【原文：U.S. stock index futures dipped on Thursday as investors shied away from risk-taking after another bout of tariff threats from U.S. President Donald Trump, while geopolitical worries and a cautious Federal Reserve further dented sentiment.】

item.title: 欧盟基金的失败使意大利苗圃的希望破灭，梅洛尼受到打击
item.description: 意大利总理乔治亚-梅洛尼（Giorgia Meloni）于 2022 年上任，她继承了双重打击--该国不仅出生率低得令人担忧，而且女性就业率也很低。【原文：When Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni took office in 2022 she inherited a double whammy - the country not only had a worryingly low birthrate, but also low female employment levels.】

item.title: 需求强劲，Birkenstock 节假日季度收入超出预期
item.description: 周四，Birkenstock 的第一季度收入超出华尔街预期，因为这家德国鞋类制造商受益于假日对其昂贵的软木凉鞋和皮鞋的强劲需求。【原文：Birkenstock beat Wall Street expectations for first-quarter revenue on Thursday, as the German footwear maker benefited from strong holiday-driven demand for its expensive cork-based sandals and shoes.】

item.title: 海尔集团将以 18 亿美元收购汽车之家近 42% 的股份
item.description: 在香港上市的汽车之家周四表示，其控股股东运晨资本开曼公司已同意以 18 亿美元的价格将其持有的汽车之家 41.91% 的股份出售给海尔集团旗下的一家公司。【原文：Hong Kong-listed Autohome said on Thursday its controlling shareholder Yun Chen Capital Cayman has agreed to sell its 41.91% stake in the company to a unit of Haier Group Corp for $1.8 billion.】

item.title: 新加坡航空公司第三季度利润增长一倍多
item.description: 新加坡航空公司（Singapore Airlines）周四公布，受印度航空公司与维斯塔拉航空公司（Vistara）合并带来的一次性收益的帮助，该公司第三季度净利润增长了近 150%。【原文：Singapore Airlines reported a near 150% jump in third-quarter net profit on Thursday, helped by a one-time gain from the Air India-Vistara merger.】

item.title: 消息人士称，TikTok 重组信任与安全团队，裁减部门员工
item.description: 三位熟知内情的消息人士周四透露，作为重组的一部分，TikTok 正在裁减其负责内容审核的信任与安全部门的全球员工。【原文：TikTok is laying off global staff at its trust and safety unit which handles content moderation as part of a restructuring, three sources familiar with the matter said on Thursday.】

item.title: 意法半导体将推出与亚马逊合作开发的数据中心光子芯片
item.description: 意法半导体（STMicroelectronics）周四表示，该公司正在推出一款新的计算机芯片，瞄准蓬勃发展的人工智能数据中心设备市场，该芯片是该公司与亚马逊网络服务部门（AWS）合作开发的。【原文：STMicroelectronics on Thursday said it is launching a new computer chip targeting the booming market for AI data centre equipment, which it has developed in cooperation with Amazon's web services arm (AWS).】

item.title: 消息人士称，美国房地产公司 CoStar 准备以 17 亿美元竞购澳大利亚 Domain 公司
item.description: 一位知情人士透露，美国房地产公司 CoStar 正准备以 27 亿澳元（17.2 亿美元）的价格竞购澳大利亚房地产分类信息公司 Domain Holdings。【原文：U.S. real estate firm CoStar is preparing an A$2.7 billion ($1.72 billion) bid for Australian property classifieds firm Domain Holdings , said a person with direct knowledge of the matter.】

item.title: 铁矿石因中国钢铁消费强劲和空头回补而上涨
item.description: 铁矿石期货周四上涨，原因是第一大消费国中国强劲的钢铁消费数据提振了市场情绪，投资者的关注点转向了矿石需求增长的前景，并刺激了一波空头回补。【原文：Iron ore futures gained on Thursday as strong steel consumption data from top consumer China boosted sentiment, shifting investor focus to prospects of growing ore demand and spurring a wave of short covering.】
